Ref: https://docs.phalcon.io/4.0/en/cache

What is Cache: 
It is a concept which stores data in a memory from which we can get data very fast. So usually we stores that data which is used most frequently in our application
Initiate cache, store in DI and then use it whereever we want to set or get data


Implement cache

Use same translation task into a new repo and do following
Whenever we initializes translation strings then first need to check if it is present in cache. If YES then pick it from cache 
If NOT then pick translation from basic approach and store in cache
